<title>USA: SEC to revamp securities trading system oversight.</title>
<headline>SEC to revamp securities trading system oversight.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission on Friday made its first step in what could be a huge overhaul of how it regulates stock exchanges and other computer-operated trading systems.</p>
<p>The agency voted to put out a nearly 150-page release informally proposing several ways in which the agency could regulate so-called alternative trading systems.</p>
<p>&quot;Services that were once the exclusive province of exchanges are provided by a growing number of private trading systems,&quot; said the agency's chairman Arthur Levitt.</p>
